{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "MRPC (Dolan and Brockett, 2005), QQP (Wang et al, 2018), and PAWS (Zhang et al, 2019) are commonly used English semantic matching datasets, used for determining semantic similarity at the sentence level.",
    "AFQMC (Xu et al, 2020b) and LCQMC (Liu et al, 2018) are commonly used large-scale Chinese datasets.",
    "Specifically, the LCQMC dataset is more inclined towards matching the intent of questions rather than semantic matching.",
    "To address the lack of other languages, PAWS-X (Yang et al, 2019) translates the PAWS dataset into 6 other languages.",
    "The most notable is the STSB dataset (Cer et al, 2017), which not only includes 10 languages but also employs continuous similarity scores as labels rather than simple binary labels."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "MRPC (Dolan and Brockett, 2005), QQP (Wang et al, 2018), and PAWS (Zhang et al, 2019) are commonly used English semantic matching datasets, used for determining semantic similarity at the sentence level.",
    "AFQMC (Xu et al, 2020b) and LCQMC (Liu et al, 2018) are commonly used large-scale Chinese datasets.",
    "To address the lack of other languages, PAWS-X (Yang et al, 2019) translates the PAWS dataset into 6 other languages.",
    "The most notable is the STSB dataset (Cer et al, 2017), which not only includes 10 languages but also employs continuous similarity scores as labels rather than simple binary labels."
